# SSH Brute Force Detection

## Objective

Detect repeated authentication attempts.

## Steps

1. Run Hydra attack:
   hydra -l root -P rockyou.txt ssh://10.10.10.40
2. Capture traffic

## Filter

tcp.port == 22

## Findings

* High number of connection attempts
* Short-lived sessions

## Indicators

* Repeated login attempts
* Consistent timing

## Conclusion

Typical brute-force attack behavior.
